10.title: Live Show 1
10.plot: The six Battle Round winners from each of Team Seal and Team Delta take to the stage for their first live performances.

11.title: Live Show 2
11.plot: The six artists from each of Team Seal and Team Delta have the results of the public votes revealed to them, with the top two artists from each team advancing to the quarter finals. The coaches then choose two of their team's remaining artists to join them. The battle round winners from Team Joel and Team Keith then take to the stage for their first live performances.

12.title: Live Show 3
12.plot: The artists from Team Joel and Team Keith have the results of the public votes revealed to them, with the top two artists from each team advancing to the quarter finals. The coaches then choose two of their team's remaining artists to join them. The four remaining artists from each of Team Seal and Team Delta then take to the stage for their next live performances.

13.title: Live Show 4
13.plot: The four remaining artists from each of Team Seal and Team Delta have the results of the public votes revealed to them, with the top artist from each team advancing to the semi finals. The coaches then choose one of their team's remaining artists to join them. The four remaining artists from Team Joel and Team Keith then take to the stage for their next live performances.

14.title: Live Semi Final
14.plot: The four remaining artists from each of Team Joel and Team Keith have the results of the public votes revealed to them, with the top artist from each team advancing to the semi finals. The coaches then choose one of their team's remaining artists to join them. The eight remaining artists then take to the stage for their next live performances, before the coaches have the sole say on which artist in their team goes through to the Grand Final.

1.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 1
1.plot: Jessie J's arrival takes the fourth season to a whole new level. The Madden brothers struggle, and Delta and Ricky prove that they are no longer rookies.

2.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 2
2.plot: The Maddens are the only team without an artist going into the second day. Jessie starts the night on fire when she picks up the first two artists. Ricky and Delta take a zen approach, and only strike when they feel that the time is right.

3.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 3
3.plot: Team Madden are trailling behind, having just one artist in their line-up going into the third day. While they look to raise their game, Jessie J takes a different tactic by putting on the brakes.

4.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 4
4.plot: The fourth day provides one of the most moving performances in The Voice's history when a wheelchair bound artist defies the odds and delivers a moment that moves everybody to tears.

5.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 5
5.plot: The blind auditions pass the halfway mark, and for both the artists and coaches, the pressure mounts. Two teenage best friends compete against each other on the stage, but can they both get the chairs to turn?

6.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 6
6.plot: The tension between Jessie and Delta heats up. The coaches are stunned by a mesmerising performance from a young busker.

7.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 7
7.plot: The mounting tension between Delta and Jessie reaches its climax when Delta takes a time out after a heated exchange during a contestant's feedback. Several contestants fail to make it through. Jessie J gives some encouragement to an audience member during a break, and gives another fan an unforgettable experience.

8.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 8
8.plot: The second last day of the blind auditions begins with the coaches feeling the heat. The Maddens, Jessie and Ricky go head to head as they try to secure their teams' final three places, but Delta is in front with two spots left on her team.

9.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 9
9.plot: As the final day of the blind auditions begins, Jessie J is searching for two more artists, while the Madden brothers, Delta and Ricky each have one place yet to be filled.

10.title: The Battles, Part 1
10.plot: The first team members go head to head in the battle ring. The coaches then have to choose who wins, who loses and who they will steal from another team.

11.title: The Battles, Part 2
11.plot: The second night of battles is a heated one as each coach puts four more artists into the battle ring, before deciding who wins, who loses and who they will steal from another team.

12.title: The Battles, Part 3
12.plot: The final four artists from each team go head to head in the battle ring. Only Delta and the Madden brothers have one more chance to steal a losing artist from another team.

13.title: The Superbattles
13.plot: The coaches give two of their final 8 artists a Fast Pass to the live finals. The other 6 artists are divided into two battle trios, where each artist sings their own song, with a common theme linking the three songs of each trio, from which the coaches choose one artist to go through to the live finals.

14.title: Live Show Final, Part 1
14.plot: The sixteen remaining artists take to the stage for their first live performances, then each coach decides which of their artists they will send through to the next round, leaving the other artists in their team to face a public vote.

15.title: Live Show Final, Part 2
15.plot: The artist from each team that receives the fewest votes is eliminated from the competition. The twelve remaining artists take to the stage for their second live performances, then their coach chooses one artist to send to the next round, leaving their other two artists to face a public vote.

16.title: Live Show Final, Part 3
16.plot: The three remaining artists in each team perform with their coach as a group, then the artist from each team that receives the fewest votes is eliminated from the competition. The eight remaining artists take to the stage for their next live performances, then their coach chooses one artist to send to the semi final, leaving the other four artists to face a public vote.

17.title: Live Semi Final
17.plot: The four artists facing the public vote take to the stage again to sing for their survival before the results of the public vote are revealed, and the two artists that receive the fewest votes are eliminated from the competition. The remaining six artists take to the stage for their next live performances, then face an instant save that will see four of them go through to the grand final.

18.title: The Grand Finale
18.plot: The final four artists take to the stage for a solo performance and a duet with their coach, then the voting lines are closed and the two artists that receive the fewest votes are eliminated from the competition. The two remaining artists perform an original song before the artist with the most votes is revealed and crowned The Voice of Australia for 2015.

1.title: Blind Auditions 1
1.plot: The quest begins to find Australia's next Voice.

2.title: Blind Auditions 2
2.plot: Newcomer Ronan Keating is the only coach without an artist going into the second night. Delta begins the night on fire by snaring two of the first three artists to perform.

3.title: Blind Auditions 3
3.plot: Night three of the blind auditions.

4.title: Blind Auditions 4
4.plot: Night four of the Blind Auditions.

5.title: Blind Auditions 5
5.plot: Night five of the Blind Auditions.

6.title: Blind Auditions 6
6.plot: We see the oldest artist ever to audition for The Voice in Australia, and a war veteran who is ready for a new chapter in her life. The coaches form a supergroup to perform a classic Spice Girls song hoping to get some miniature lookalikes of themselves to turn their chairs.

7.title: Blind Auditions 7
7.plot: As the auditions continue, we haven't seen the last of the firsts - a former artist from The Voice Kids (2014) returns to the stage, the coaches are blown away by the first ever trio, and when the pressure gets too much for one artist, it brings the production to a stop. Another artist from a previous season returns determined to put in a chair-turning performance second time around.

8.title: Blind Auditions 8
8.plot: The blind auditions start to draw to a close and one of the coaches completes their team. Two sisters perform separately, but will both of them get through? Jessie J makes an audition of her own, singing a massive track from Whitney Houston to try to get the other coaches to turn.

9.title: Blind Auditions 9
9.plot: The final night of the blind auditions begins with just four spots remaining to be filled as Jessie, Delta and Ronan search for artists to complete their teams. An electrifying performance from one artist gets all of the coaches joining her on the stage.

10.title: The Battles, Part 1
10.plot: The Battle Rounds kick off with a bang when the coaches join forces to deliver a knockout performance and the first eight battle pairs face the ultimate singing showdown in the battle ring. Among the artists fighting for a spot on their coach's team are two Disney princesses who go head to head for a place on Team Jessie J. After each performance, the coaches decide who wins, who loses and who they will save from elimination.

11.title: The Battles, Part 2
11.plot: The next eight battle pairs go head-to-head in the battle ring. Trio The Koi Boys take on Ilisavani Cava in the biggest battle ever. A battle between sisters Jasmin Jade and Nada-Leigh Nasser ends with a shock result.

12.title: The Battles, Part 3
12.plot: The final eight battle pairs, including five artists that got all four chairs to turn in the blind auditions, go into the battle ring to fight to remain on their coach's team and advance to the Superbattles. Some favourite artists from the blind auditions lose their battles in shock results, while one team's Save leads to a clash between the coaches.

13.title: The Superbattles
13.plot: The eight remaining artists on each team have just one chance to make it to the live shows. Four artists take to the battle ring at once, each singing their own song, with a common theme linking the songs in each quartet. With only two artists from each quartet able to go through, there will be some emotional victories and shock exits.

14.title: The Live Shows, Round 1
14.plot: The sixteen remaining artists take to the stage for their first live performances, then each coach decides which of their artists they will send through to the next round, leaving the other artists in their team to face a public vote.

15.title: The Live Shows, Round 2
15.plot: The artist from each team that receives the fewest votes is eliminated from the competition. The twelve remaining artists then sing to keep their place in the competition before they all face a public vote. Ronan Keating takes to the stage for a very special performance.

16.title: The Live Shows, Round 3
16.plot: The artist from each team that receives the fewest votes is eliminated from the competition. The eight remaining artists then sing to keep their place in the competition before they all face a public vote.

17.title: The Semi Finals - Live
17.plot: The one artist from each team that receives more votes advances to the final six. The four remaining artists then sing to keep their place in the competition before facing an instant save from which the two artists that receive the fewest votes are eliminated from the competition. The remaining six artists take to the stage for their next live performances, then face another instant save that will see four of them go through to the grand final. Delta Goodrem performs her latest single and Mike Posner makes a guest appearance.

18.title: The Grand Finale - Live
18.plot: The final four artists take to the stage for a solo performance and a duet with their coach, then the voting lines are closed and the two artists that receive the fewest votes are eliminated from the competition. The two remaining artists perform an original song before the artist with the most votes is revealed and crowned The Voice of Australia for 2016.

11.title: Knockouts 1
11.plot: The competition moves into a brand new phase when the Knockouts begin. Teenage wonder Lucy Sugerman goes up against Brooke Schubert and powerhouse Liz Conde in a breathtaking Sia contest. Crowd favourite Judah Kelly returns.

12.title: Knockouts 2
12.plot: The next batch of artists compete for a place in the next Battle rounds. Queensland teenager Brittania Clifford-Pugh faces up against 17-year-old Hoseah Partsch and the enigmatic James Banks in one of the series' most emotional moments.

13.title: Knockouts 3
13.plot: The Knockout rounds conclude with blind girl Lara Nakhale stepping up against Annalise Walker, who got all four chairs to turn, and stuntman Russel Francis. Country powerhouse Lyn Bowtell takes on a classic Beatles song.

14.title: Battles 1
14.plot: The first 6 pairs of artists compete against each other, in sudden death contests with no second chances, for a place in the live finals. Among the battles are the two youngest artists Lucy and Camryn, as well as Sarah versus Lynn and Spencer versus Russ.

15.title: Battles 2
15.plot: The final 6 pairs of artists compete against each other, in sudden death contests with no second chances, for a place in the live finals. Among the battles, opera singer Nathan is pitted against Hoseah, and Judah and Kelsie tackle a Miley Cyrus song.

16.title: Live Finals 1: Top 12
16.plot: The 12 battle winners take to the stage for their first live performances. The results of the public vote, held through The Voice app, are then revealed, and the two artists with the fewest votes compete in a sudden-death sing off before facing an instant vote that will send the artist with fewer votes home.

17.title: Live Finals 2: Top 11
17.plot: The 11 remaining artists take to the stage for their next live performances. The results of the public vote, held through The Voice app, are then revealed, and the two artists with the fewest votes compete in a sudden-death sing off before facing an instant vote that will send the artist with fewer votes home. The Veronicas make a guest appearance.

18.title: Live Finals 3: Top 10
18.plot: The 10 remaining artists take to the stage for their next live performances. The results of the public vote, held through The Voice app, are then revealed, and the seven artists with the most votes go through to the semi-final, leaving the other three to compete in a sudden-death sing off before facing an instant vote that will see the artist with the most votes take the final spot in the semi-final, sending the other two artists home.

19.title: Live Semi-Final
19.plot: The eight remaining artists take to the stage for their next live performances. The results of the public vote, held through The Voice app, are then revealed, and the two artists that receive the fewest votes are eliminated from the competition. The remaining six artists then sing to keep their place in the competition before facing another public vote that will see four of them go through to the grand final. Last year's winner Alfie Arcuri performs his new single and Jessica Mauboy also makes a guest appearance.

20.title: Live Grand Final
20.plot: The final four artists take to the stage for a solo performance and a duet with their coach, then the voting lines are closed and the two artists that receive the fewest votes are eliminated from the competition. The two remaining artists perform an original song before the artist with the most votes is revealed and crowned The Voice of Australia for 2017.

locations: Fox Studios, Moore Park, Sydney, New South Wales, Australia
imdb.plot outline: On 'The Voice' the four superstar musician coaches begin to select teams of fourteen based solely on an artist's voice. Joel Madden, Benji Madden, Delta Goodrem, and Ricky Martin, are competing as coaches - each one hoping to discover, and nurture Australia's next great voice.
imdb.title: The Voice
plot: Contestants compete in a singing competition that focuses on the quality of their voice.::_The Voice_ (qv) Australia

On '_The Voice_ (qv)' the four superstar musician coaches begin to select teams of fourteen based solely on an artist's voice. 'Joel Madden' (qv), 'Benji Madden' (qv), 'Delta Goodrem' (qv), and 'Ricky Martin' (qv), are competing as coaches - each one hoping to discover, and nurture Australia's next great voice.::_The Voice_ (qv) Australia

There are four coaches, who are all famous in the music industry. During the blind auditions these coaches will turn around in their chairs when they hear a performer they want in their team. If there are more coaches who want a performer, he or she gets to choose who they want as their coach. During the battles there will be two contestants from the same team up against eachother. The coach then has to choose one of them to get through to the live shows.::immevangorp
